WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
New York, June, 1800.

00:08.000 --> 00:11.000
It's seven o'clock on a warm summer morning,

00:12.000 --> 00:14.000
a ship thriving in New York.

00:15.000 --> 00:18.000
Its name is the Red Rose.

00:20.000 --> 00:25.000
Two of the people on it are Sam Tinker and his daughter, Jenny.

00:26.000 --> 00:28.000
Sam and Jenny are English,

00:29.000 --> 00:33.000
but now they're starting a new life in America.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.000
Look, Dad!

00:36.000 --> 00:37.000
Says Jenny.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.000
We're here!

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
We're really here!

00:43.000 --> 00:46.000
The Tinkers say goodbye to all their friends.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
Then they leave the Red Rose.

00:50.000 --> 00:57.000
There are lots of people, horses and carts beside the ship.

00:58.000 --> 00:59.000
Sam looks at them.

01:00.000 --> 01:04.000
Yes, we're here, he thinks.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.000
But now what?

01:07.000 --> 01:09.000
We haven't got any money.

01:11.000 --> 01:14.000
He stops a young man with a green coat.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.000
Excuse me?

01:17.000 --> 01:18.000
He says.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
I'm looking for a job.

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
The man turns to his right.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
Talk to Jack Crane.

01:29.000 --> 01:30.000
He answers.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Jack cranes a farmer.

01:34.000 --> 01:40.000
He has a long, thin face and only three fingers on his right hand.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.000
He listens to Sam's story.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
Then he takes off his hat.

01:48.000 --> 01:49.000
Okay.

01:50.000 --> 01:51.000
He says.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
You can both have jobs.

01:55.000 --> 01:59.000
I need a new man to work in the field.

02:00.000 --> 02:04.000
And we want someone to help in the kitchen too.

02:05.000 --> 02:07.000
Isn't that right, blue sky?

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
There's an Indian girl on top of the cart.

02:15.000 --> 02:19.000
Yes, she says, and smiles at Jenny.

02:24.000 --> 02:30.000
Two hours later, the tinkerers leave New York with Jack Crane and blue sky.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
They're both very happy.

02:34.000 --> 02:38.000
How far is it to your farm, Mr. Crane?

02:39.000 --> 02:40.000
Ask Sam.

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
80 kilometers.

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
Jack Crane answers.

02:48.000 --> 02:50.000
They drive all afternoon.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
Jenny's sitting next to Sam.

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
She's tired, but she doesn't want to sleep.

02:59.000 --> 03:02.000
This is America, she thinks.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
And now, I'm American.

03:07.000 --> 03:11.000
After six hours, Jack Crane stops the cart.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
Well, there it is.

03:17.000 --> 03:21.000
He says, Jenny stands up.

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
It's evening now, and the sun's going down.

03:27.000 --> 03:35.000
In front of them, there are lots of beautiful yellow fields and a big farmhouse.

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
Jenny looks to her left.

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
Where's that smoke coming from?

03:43.000 --> 03:44.000
She asks.

03:45.000 --> 03:50.000
That's the Indian village answers blue sky.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
My family lives there.

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
The next day, the tinkerers start work.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.000
Jenny helps blue sky in the farmhouse.

04:05.000 --> 04:09.000
First, the two girls cook everyone's breakfast.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Then they make all the beds.

04:14.000 --> 04:17.000
After that, they clean the kitchen floor.

04:26.000 --> 04:30.000
At the same time, Sam's working in the fields.

04:31.000 --> 04:35.000
After four or five hours, he stops for a minute.

04:37.000 --> 04:39.000
What are you stopping for?

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
asks Jack Crane.

04:43.000 --> 04:45.000
Come on, get back to work.

04:47.000 --> 04:51.000
Sam and Jenny have only one free day every week.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.000
Sunday.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
It's blue skies free day, too.

04:57.000 --> 04:59.000
That's when she visits her family.

05:01.000 --> 05:04.000
One Sunday, Jenny goes with her.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.000
She makes a lot of new friends.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
She meets the village chief, too.

05:12.000 --> 05:13.000
Silver Cloud.

05:15.000 --> 05:18.000
He has a beautiful wife and a young son.

05:20.000 --> 05:24.000
After that first visit, Jenny often goes to the village.

05:27.000 --> 05:30.000
She starts to learn some Indian words, too.

05:31.000 --> 05:35.000
Jenny's always happy with her new Indian friends.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
But she's not happy on the farm.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Sam's unhappy, too.

05:43.000 --> 05:47.000
I don't want to work here on Jack Crane's farm anymore.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.000
He says one evening.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.000
I want to work on my farm.

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
Tinker's farm.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.000
I know, Dad.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
Jenny answers.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.000
Then she thinks.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.000
But how?

06:05.000 --> 06:07.000
We can't buy any land.

06:08.000 --> 06:11.000
Jack Crane pays us only two dollars a week.

06:12.000 --> 06:17.000
Four days later, Jenny and Blue Skye are making the beds.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Suddenly, they hear something.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.000
Two men are shouting.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.000
Jenny looks out of the window.

06:27.000 --> 06:32.000
She can see Jack Crane and her father in front of the farmhouse.

06:33.000 --> 06:36.000
Jack Crane's face is very red.

06:38.000 --> 06:39.000
Do it!

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
He shouts.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
No! I'm not going to!

06:46.000 --> 06:47.000
Sam shouts back.

06:48.000 --> 06:52.000
It's Sunday, and I don't work on Sundays.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.000
You do it!

06:55.000 --> 06:58.000
Jenny runs downstairs and out of the house.

06:59.000 --> 07:02.000
There's a strong wind and it's raining.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.000
What's happening?

07:06.000 --> 07:07.000
She asks her father.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
We're leaving in the morning.

07:12.000 --> 07:13.000
Sam answers.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
He's walking very fast.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.000
Jenny looks at him.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.000
But how are we going to eat?

07:23.000 --> 07:24.000
We haven't got any money.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.000
Sam doesn't answer.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.000
His eyes are cold and hard.

07:33.000 --> 07:37.000
That evening, Jenny and Blue Skye go to the Indian village.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
This is going to be my last visit.

07:44.000 --> 07:45.000
Jenny thinks.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.000
Blue Skye's sad too.

07:49.000 --> 07:51.000
She doesn't want to lose her friend.

07:53.000 --> 07:56.000
The two girls say nothing for 20 minutes.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
Then Blue Skye stops her horse.

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
She can see something in the river to their right.

08:06.000 --> 08:07.000
It's a small boy.

08:09.000 --> 08:10.000
Help!

08:11.000 --> 08:12.000
He's shouting.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.000
I can't swim!

08:16.000 --> 08:17.000
Help me!

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
Please!

08:20.000 --> 08:24.000
It's the cheap sun, says Blue Skye.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.000
What are we going to?

08:28.000 --> 08:32.000
But before she can say another word, Jenny gets off her horse.

08:34.000 --> 08:35.000
I'm coming!

08:36.000 --> 08:37.000
She shouts.

08:38.000 --> 08:41.000
Then she jumps into the cold river.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.000
Help!

08:45.000 --> 08:46.000
Shout to the boy.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.000
Jenny swims to him.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
His head is going under the water.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
She puts one arm around him.

08:58.000 --> 08:59.000
It's okay.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.000
She says.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.000
You're safe now.

09:05.000 --> 09:11.000
Half an hour later, Jenny and Blue Skye arrive at the Indian village.

09:12.000 --> 09:14.000
The chief comes to meet them.

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
But I don't understand.

09:20.000 --> 09:21.000
He says to Blue Skye.

09:23.000 --> 09:25.000
Why is my son with you?

09:26.000 --> 09:29.000
And why are he and the English girl wet?

09:31.000 --> 09:34.000
Blue Skye tells him the story.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.000
After that, the chief's very happy.

09:40.000 --> 09:42.000
He smiles at Jenny.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
How can I thank you?

09:46.000 --> 09:47.000
He says.

09:48.000 --> 09:51.000
Please, let me give you something.

09:52.000 --> 09:53.000
Anything.

09:56.000 --> 10:00.000
At nine o'clock, Sam's putting some boots into a bag.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
What's going to happen tomorrow?

10:05.000 --> 10:06.000
He thinks.

10:07.000 --> 10:09.000
Suddenly, the door opens.

10:13.000 --> 10:14.000
It's Jenny.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.000
Come with me, Dad.

10:17.000 --> 10:18.000
She says.

10:19.000 --> 10:21.000
I want to show you something.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.000
Sam looks at his daughter.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.000
Her eyes are bright.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.000
And she's smiling.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
What are you talking about?

10:34.000 --> 10:35.000
He asks.

10:36.000 --> 10:40.000
There isn't time for any questions, says Jenny.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.000
Come on!

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
She takes her father to a hill.

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
At the top, she says.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.000
Look!

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
Can you see that land over there?

10:55.000 --> 10:56.000
Yes.

10:57.000 --> 10:58.000
Sam answers.

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
Then Jenny tells him about Silver Cloud's son.

11:03.000 --> 11:06.000
After she finishes, Sam says.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.000
You mean?

11:09.000 --> 11:10.000
Yes!

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
Jenny smiled at her father.

11:15.000 --> 11:19.000
The Indians are giving us our own farm.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.000
Tinker's farm.

11:23.000 --> 11:24.000
Oh, Dad.

11:24.000 --> 11:26.000
Isn't it wonderful?

11:27.000 --> 11:30.000
Now we can really start a new life.

